      "content": "I hear how deeply painful and isolating this feeling of erasure is, and it makes complete sense that you feel exhausted from maintaining a facade when the pressure to be \"perfect\" has become unbearable. When the only version of yourself that people see is a mask you're forced to wear, it's natural to feel like the real person underneath has vanished along with it. You are not alone in this struggle, and your feelings of emptiness are valid responses to a situation that feels overwhelming. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help you navigate these intense emotions and find a way to reconnect with yourself outside of the expectations others placed on you.",
